data.title: Dive Bar on Main street in RRock
data.text: Great little hole in the wall! Funky little bar with great staff and cold drinks. We went on a Saturday when it was 100 degrees outside for a cold beer. The bartender let us try several of the local brews. It's an old wooden bar with no frills and they need to do some dusting as there is dirt everywhere but the cold drinks and great vibe will have us coming back again.

data.title: Great local little divey bar, cheap, good pour, nice folks.
data.text: Cute downtown area, bar is slow by day, and livens up after 9pm. Drinks are good and cheap. People are nice and eager to please.

data.title: If you can't go to DT Austin, come here
data.text:
If you don't want to drive all the way down to Austin's 6th street then you can always try out DT Round Rock. 

The bar scene is growing more and more every day, they just built another bar "The Rock" sports bar, and there are several restaurants there to enjoy. 

Quinn's has live music most of the nights and 2 pool tables in the back, its pretty much an all in one establishment. 

Overall its a quaint little night life, nothing over the top but a hell of a lot closer than 6th street.

data.title: Drinking Hole
data.text: This is a semi decent drinking hole to get lost with some buddies.  It is very homely, though the people there can sometimes be a little obnoxious to strangers.

data.title: Awesome Night Life
data.text: First time I've been to Quinn's and I was NOT disappointed! The bartender put on a show blowing a giant fire ball across the bar. There was a fun live band, people dancing, really unique drinks, cool wallpaper in the ladies restroom, pool in the back - it was really cool. I can't wait to go back!

data.title: loud small and smoky
data.text: the combination of a band thats way too close and smokers makes this a niche market for people who love loud rock and can stand cigarette smoke.
